---
description: menofhunger-www core conventions (Nuxt + PrimeVue)
alwaysApply: true
---

## Backend + API calling
- **No Nuxt server API** for product features (`server/api/**`): use `menofhunger-api`
- Call the backend via `useApiClient()` (no ad-hoc fetch/base URLs)
- Success envelope: `{ data: T }` (+ optional `pagination` for lists)

## When you add/change an API response
- Update API DTOs: `menofhunger-api/src/common/dto/**`
- Update web types: `menofhunger-www/types/api.ts`
- Run `npx nuxi typecheck` + `node scripts/validate-api-types.mjs`

## Layout rule (pick one)
- Never show both the layout title bar **and** an in-page header
- If you need an in-page header, set route meta to hide the top bar (e.g. `hideTopBar: true`)

## Links
- Every internal navigation MUST render a real `<a>` so right-click / cmd+click / middle-click "Open in new tab" works. See rule `40-internal-links.mdc` and skill `.cursor/skills/clickable-rows/SKILL.md`.

## Real-time first
- Pages that show mutable server state must wire a websocket subscription via `usePresence()` AND fetch on mount/activation. HTTP is the on-load sync; sockets are the live feed. See rule `60-realtime-first.mdc` and skill `.cursor/skills/realtime-page-sync/SKILL.md`.

## Admin
- Hide admin pages from non-admins (**404** in middleware)

